thread.title: High school girls soccer had highest concussion rate for decade
thread.title_full: High school girls soccer had highest concussion rate for decade

author: Benjamin Raven | braven@mlive.com
title: High school girls soccer had highest concussion rate for decade
text: High school female athletes, in general, suffered concussions at a "significantly higher" rate than boys. The study presented points to the lack of protective gear in high school soccer as a potential cause for the greater risk of concussions.
